	abstract = {This work revisits the Semideﬁne Programming (SDP) relaxation of the AC power ﬂow equations in light of recent results illustrating the beneﬁts of bounds propagation, valid inequalities, and the Convex Quadratic (QC) relaxation. By integrating all of these results into the SDP model a new hybrid relaxation is proposed, which combines the beneﬁts from all of these recent works. This strengthened SDP formulation is evaluated on 71 AC Optimal Power Flow test cases from the NESTA archive and is shown to have an optimality gap of less than 1\% on 63 cases. This new hybrid relaxation closes 50\% of the open cases considered, leaving only 8 for future investigation.},
